---
import Donator from '$lib/components/Donator.astro';
import IconPatreon from '~icons/custom/patreon';
import IconGitHub from '~icons/lucide/github';
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';
import Page from '$lib/layouts/Page.astro';

const current = await getCollection('supporters', (s) => s.data.active);
const past = await getCollection('supporters', (s) => !s.data.active);
---

<Page>
	<section class="header">
		<h1>Sponsors 💙</h1>

		<p>
			Hey, I'm Willow (also sometimes known as GHOST) and I'm working on
			Open Source projects and community events. Your support helps me
			fund this work, and the events. 💙
		</p>

		<p>
			I'm part of the npmx core team, working to build a better frontend
			and all around npm experience. We have a massive community of people
			who love npm and want to make it better. I help work on the project
			direction, with a focus on code review and the underlying npm data
			itself.
		</p>

		<p>
			I work on e18e, helping with the upcoming data project as well as
			the module replacements. e18e is a community group focusing on
			improving the performance of the javascript ecosystem at large.
			Opening PRs to popular packages and projects to help improve
			performance, and remove unnecessary dependencies as well as giving
			people the tools to be more mindful about the code they're
			consuming.
		</p>

		<p>
			I help organise the Svelte community, being an ambassador as well as
			moderator of the Discord and maintainer of the Discord bot. I help
			organise Svelte London, which is the most active in person Svelte
			meetup, happening nearly every month. I also attend multiple other
			meetups in London, as well as multiple conferences, helping grow the
			communities and share the projects we're working on.
		</p>

		<p>
			Your sponsorship will help me devote as much time to working on
			code, with communities, and paying for travel to and for organising
			community events. However, that being said you don't have to sponsor
			me directly. You can sponsor collectives such as the
			<a href="https://opencollective.com/antfu">Anthony Fu Fund</a>. You
			can also give your time to contribute to projects (code or
			otherwise), help organise, attend events. Everything we do together
			helps support and grow this thing we love 💙
		</p>

		<a
			title="GitHub Sponsors"
			aria-label="GitHub Sponsors"
			href="https://github.com/sponsors/ghostdevv"
			target="_blank"
			class="button icon"
		>
			<IconGitHub /> GitHub Sponsors
		</a>

		<a
			title="Patreon"
			aria-label="Patreon"
			href="https://www.patreon.com/onlyspaceghost"
			target="_blank"
			class="button icon"
		>
			<IconPatreon /> Patreon
		</a>

		<hr />

		<section class="column g16">
			<h3 style="font-size: calc(1.275rem + .3vw);">
				Current Supporters
			</h3>

			<div class="row wrap">
				{
					current
						.sort((a, b) => a.data.name.localeCompare(b.data.name))
						.map((p) => (
							<Donator name={p.data.name} src={p.data.pfp} />
						))
				}
			</div>

			<h3 style="font-size: calc(1.275rem + .3vw);">Past Supporters</h3>

			<div class="row wrap">
				{
					past

						.sort((a, b) => a.data.name.localeCompare(b.data.name))
						.map((p) => (
							<Donator name={p.data.name} src={p.data.pfp} slim />
						))
				}
			</div>
		</section>
	</section>

	<style>
		.header {
			h1 {
				margin-bottom: 22px;
			}

			p {
				max-width: 800px;
				font-size: 17px;
				margin: 14px 0px;
			}
		}
	</style>
</Page>
